There are a number of Darwin Day events going on in the Palmetto State, both today and throughout the week.  You can go to the <a href="http://www.sc-scied.org/EE/index.php">South Carolinians for Science Education</a> website for a complete run-down of the events and links to the individual flyers.  Events will be held at <a href="http://www.sc-scied.org/EE/index.php/scied/comments/darwin_day_celebration_at_furman_university/">Furman</a>, the <a href="http://www.cofc.edu/%7Edillonr/DarwinWeekVII.html">College of Charleston</a>, and <a href="http://www.thewilsonshouse.com/science/SCSE/CUDarwinDay07.doc">Clemson</a>.  Kenneth Miller will also be <a href="http://www.thewilsonshouse.com/science/SCSE/KenMilleratCU.doc">speaking</a> in Clemson next Monday.
